(2839, 1, '2016-07-24 18:44:03', '2016-07-24 18:44:03', '<strong>Vijay Sharma ‚Äì Founder & CEO</strong>\r\nFounder & CEO of Aelix Systems Inc. Acquired by eOn Communications  in 2005\r\nCTO and VP of Engineering for public listed companies and startups\r\nDirector of Engineering at Avaya Inc., number one market leader in real time collaboration\r\nVisionary leader in innovation of real-time communication & collaboration platforms\r\n<strong>Dr. Jagdish Patel MD, FACC‚Äì Chief Medical Officer</strong>\r\nCardiology / QI initiatives / Telemedicine\r\nPresident of Kishwaukee Cardiology\r\nAdvisor to many leading hospitals in USA & India.\r\n<strong>Amit Sharma ‚Äì VP of Business Development</strong>\r\n 8 plus years of experience  in SaaS sales, B2B Sales  with JC Penney, Ralph Lauren and Macy.\r\n<strong>Amar Sharma ‚Äì VP of Sales</strong>\r\nTop sales performer with the Gannett group, a leading U.S. media company  \r\n<strong>Ved Bhatnagar ‚Äì VP of Engineering</strong>\r\n15+ years experience in developing Real Time Communication products and services, including Avaya''s Aura‚Äôs conferencing solution (integrated Audio, Video, Web Conferencing solution for large enterprises\r\n<strong>Yash Arora ‚Äì Director of Engineering, India</strong>\r\nYash Arora has over 14 years of experience developing leading edge web and mobile applications.\r\nIn addition to leading engineering teams in India, he is also a hands-on technical contributor\r\nINSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(2886, 1, '2016-11-14 05:42:41', '2016-11-14 05:42:41', 'SILICON VALLEY, CALIFORNIA - 06/22/2016 (PRESS RELEASE JET) ‚Äî Today, TeleHealth365 Inc. announced an angel round of funding from a private investor. The company is a provider of SaaS (software as a service) HIPAA-compliant secure video conferencing solution for healthcare. The funding is focused on growing sales, marketing and taking the company to the next level worldwide.\r\n\r\nPresently, TeleHealth365 SaaS secure video solution is being used in the USA, India, Bangladesh and the Middle East. The business is seeing major growth throughout these markets. ‚ÄúFunding will allow us to keep pace with the opportunities we are seeing, serve more doctors and patients, and grow the company by leaps and bounds,‚Äù said TeleHealth365 Vice President of Business Development, Amit Sharma.\r\n\r\nIndividual healthcare providers and hospitals are using secure video conferencing to schedule virtual office visits with patients in their communities, especially in rural areas where hospitals and clinics may not have an on-staff specialist.\r\n\r\n‚ÄúThere is no substitute for talking with patients when and where they need. Patients want person-to-person help with their medications, their questions and their concerns. Two-way video enables doctors, hospitals and healthcare providers to engage with their patients personally in everything from routine checkups and home health services to telestroke assessments and surgical consults,‚Äù said TeleHealth365 founder, and CEO, Vijay Sharma.\r\n\r\n‚ÄúTeleHealth365 Inc has built a cloud platform that allows two-way video consultation over the internet, available anywhere in the world and at a compelling cost structure. There is no expensive equipment to purchase as it works on your laptop, tablet, smartphone, iPad and iPhone. It‚Äôs exciting now because healthcare providers can serve their patients anytime, anywhere, including in their homes. Telehealth365‚Äôs ability to integrate with EMR‚Äôs is a stepping stone to growth of Telemedicine in USA.‚Äù\r\n\r\nAccording to PWC (http://www.pwc.com), healthcare systems around the world are dealing with depleting resources at a time when demand for healthcare is rapidly rising. Governments face growing pressure to reduce costs without impacting quality or access to care. At the same time, the World Economic Forum and OECD predict BRICS will see a 117% increase in health spending over the next decade, while U.S. health expenditures are projected to increase by $3.5 trillion between 2010 and 2040.\r\n\r\nTechnological advances can help to contain or even reduce these costs, while providing quality access to care. Inpatient care is moving to outpatient service. Mobile devices and apps are enabling greater patient engagement in their own care. Patients can monitor their health at home with devices that send reports wirelessly to their physician. Remote monitoring, telemedicine and mobile devices will help reduce the burden on health systems. Improved analytics will also provide healthcare professionals with greater insight. With knowledge of patient flow and care delivery pathways, health professionals can provide the most appropriate individualised care more efficiently.\r\n\r\n<strong>About TeleHealth365 Inc.</strong>\r\n\r\nTeleHealth365 Inc is headquartered in Silicon Valley, California. It serves ‚Äúfor profit healthcare providers‚Äù and NGOs throughout the world, connecting patients to doctors anytime, anywhere. <strong>(</strong><a href="https://www.telehealth365.com/"><strong>https://www.TeleHealth365.com</strong></a><strong>).</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>For contact: </strong><a href="mailto:Usha.Sharma@TeleHealth365.com"><strong>Usha.Sharma@TeleHealth365.com</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Media Contacts:</strong>\r\n\r\nCompany Name: TeleHealth365 Inc\r\nFull Name: Usha Sharma\r\nEmail Address: usha.sharma@telehealth365.com\r\nWebsite: <a href="https://www.telehealth365.com/" target="_blank">https://www.TeleHealth365.com</a>', 'TeleHealth365 Receives First Round of Angel Funding', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2885-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-14 05:42:41', '2016-11-14 05:42:41', '', 2885, 'https://www.telehealth365.com/2885-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2887, 1, '2016-11-14 05:45:13', '2016-11-14 05:45:13', 'SAN JOSE, CA, October 18, 2016 <b>/24-7PressRelease/</b> -- TeleHealth365 today announced that it has acquired WideState Medicare Tourism LLP for an undisclosed amount of cash and stocks. WideState Medicare Tourism is now a division of Telehealth365, Inc operating from India. This will allow TeleHealth365 to enter the medical tourism market which will generate $143.8 billion by 2022, according to Allied Research.\r\n\r\nTeleHealth365''s secure video solution is being used in the USA and globally. The business is seeing major growth throughout these markets. Individual healthcare providers and hospitals are using secure video conferencing to schedule virtual office visits with patients in their communities, especially in rural areas where hospitals and clinics may not have an on-staff specialist.\r\n\r\n"TeleHealth365 has built a cloud platform that allows two-way video consultation over the internet, available anywhere in the world and at a compelling cost structure. There is no expensive equipment to purchase as it works on your laptop, tablet, smartphone, iPad and iPhone. It''s exciting now because healthcare providers can serve their patients anytime, anywhere, including in their homes," said TeleHealth365''s CEO and founder, Vijay Sharma. "TeleHealth365''s ability to integrate with EMRs is a stepping stone to the growth of telemedicine in the USA."\r\n\r\n"We conducted an exhaustive search for a healthcare management company that would complement TeleHealth365 vision of making healthcare accessible to hundreds of millions of people in Asia, Africa and the Middle East. We are delighted to have Dr. Alekh Sharma (Founder of WideState Medicare Tourism LLP) and his team on board. Dr. Alekh, as General Manager, will focus on Asia, Africa and the Middle East healthcare market," said Vijay Sharma. "The Wide State Medicare team has grown a fantastic business centered on connecting the world''s most prestigious hospitals with patients across the globe."\r\n\r\nDr. Alekh Sharma of WideState Medicare said, "I have always admired TeleHealth365 for its innovation and dynamic leadership team, and I''m honored to be joining their team. I have tremendous respect for Vijay (CEO), Dr. Jagdish Patel (CMO) and his team, and I look forward to working with them."\r\n\r\nAbout TeleHealth365 Inc.\r\nTeleHealth365 Inc. is headquartered in Silicon Valley, California. It serves "for profit healthcare providers" and NGOs throughout the world, connecting patients to doctors anytime, anywhere. (<a class="link_release_content" href="https://www.telehealth365.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">https://www.TeleHealth365.com</a>).\r\n\r\nMedia Contacts:\r\nCompany Name: TeleHealth365 Inc\r\nFull Name: Usha Sharma\r\nEmail Address: <a class="link_release_content" href="mailto:Usha.Sharma@TeleHealth365.com" rel="nofollow">Usha.Sharma@TeleHealth365.com</a>\r\nWebsite: <a class="link_release_content" href="https://www.telehealth365.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">https://www.TeleHealth365.com</a>', 'TeleHealth365 Inc Buys WideState Medicare Tourism', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'telehealth365-inc-buys-widestate-medicare-tourism', '', '', '2016-11-17 13:53:33', '2016-11-17 13:53:33', '', 0, 'https://www.telehealth365.com/?p=2887', 0, 'post', '', 0),
