(2180, 1, '2015-04-30 11:48:57', '2015-04-30 11:48:57', 'AS SEEN IN TV NEWS\n\n&nbsp;\n\nAND NEWSPAPERS\n\nTeleHealth365 Inc, a Silicon Valley company, plans to shake up and revolutionize the healthcare industry by\nproviding free video conferencing to physicians. The technology is secure and HIPAA compliant, a distinct\nadvantage over other video consumer offerings.\n\n<a href="http://www.pr.com/press-release/609473" target="_blank">Morgan Hill, CA, March 10, 2015 --(PR.com)</a>-- TeleHealth365, a Silicon Valley company founded by visionary\nVijay Sharma, is pioneering technology to solve the growing crisis of healthcare costs in the United States. In\n2014, the US spent $3.8 trillion on healthcare and the number has been increasing each year for the past decade\n(Forbes.com). Healthcare projections indicate that the shortage of physicians, chronic diseases and an aging\npopulation will place additional demands on the existing healthcare system. Hospitals spent $41.3 billion between\nJanuary and November 2011 to treat patients readmitted within 30 days of discharge, according to the Agency for\nHealthcare Research and Quality. $24 billion was due to Medicare readmissions which likely could have been\navoided with better post-discharge care.\nTeleHealth365 has released its flagship product, OmniPresence 2.0, which connects patients at home with their\nhealthcare providers anywhere in the world. OmniPresence provides secure video-conferencing that is fully\nencrypted and HIPAA compliant, unlike other consumer grade video systems which are not secure and do not\nmeet the stringent privacy requirements needed for the exchange of health information. The service resides in the\ncloud and there is no software to install. It is easy to use and no special equipment is needed beyond your\neveryday tablet, smartphone or PC.\nOmniPresence allows nurse practitioners or hospital doctors to monitor post-surgical patients in the convenience\nof their own homes, to check on their recovery, medications, and rehabilitation process. This increases the\npotential of reducing the readmissions which are avoidable, and enhances recovery for patients. CEO Vijay\nSharma calls the service, ?Doctor-At-HomeTM,? and believes it is a potent tool optimizing the physician?s\navailability while benefitting the patient?s wellbeing.\nTeleHealth365 plans to shake-up and revolutionize the healthcare industry by offering their secure video\nconferencing solution free to all medical practitioners. For more information, visit?http://www.TeleHealth365.com.\nContact: Usha Sharma\nTel: 408.375.5157\nTeleHealth365 Inc,\n18510, Serra Court,\nMorgan Hill, CA 95037\n\n&nbsp;', 'Doctor-at-Home to Reduce Hospital Readmissions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2175-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-04-30 11:48:57', '2015-04-30 11:48:57', '', 2175, 'https://www.telehealth365.com/2175-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
